{
  "stem": "26699.5",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And with the passport, which was valid from Romania to Czechoslovakia via Hungary and back, to be returned, and through a certain defined route, which needed to be watched, we prepared ourselves.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "We filled the car with food and all what was necessary for a trip of two weeks.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And without telling anybody about our intention of escaping-- particularly we didn't tell our parents because they would have been in a state to know that we risk our lives or our freedom.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "The minimum sentence for such an attempt to escape was five years in jail, or, if you tried to do this in a more adventurous way, trying to break through or to go through the Iron Curtain, you can be shot dead.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "But we planned our escape.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "We arrived safely to Hungary from Romania.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And it was a possibility that we can escape from Hungary to Yugoslavia.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "Arriving through the Hungarian Yugoslavian border my wife, who spoke Hungarian through her parents, asked the Hungarian guards if there is a possibility to try to visit somebody in Yugoslavia, not telling them that we intend to go.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And she was lucky to find somebody who understood what we intend to do to advise her not even to dream to try such a thing, because the border is sealed.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "So it was second time after the first time in Iasi when my mother saved my life with knowledge of a foreign language, that a foreign language looked to be very useful, sometimes saving your life.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we went on our route to Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We arrived at Bratislava And there is the border over the Danube River to Austria.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was very hesitant to go straight to the border.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
